race.comment: NYMPHADORA (5) frustrating mare who resumed with an eye-catching fourth over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Lone victory came on her home track, and she gets her chance over this trip. NESRINE (4) back for her second campaign when she monstered her rivals with a sharp maiden victory over 1100m at this track in fast time. Only needs to hold that form to win again. LAND BANK (3) came up from Victoria second-up when a dominant winner from off the pace over 1100m at Scone. Hitting his straps now and gets a much better set-up today. MARGIN CALL (7) heavily supported on debut when a commanding winner over 1000m at Canberra. Has the upside to test this field.
